    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>One of the large divisions of an army; military units in the form of a headquarters and a large body of soldiers commanded by a field-grade officer. The term has been used variously in Western culture for centuries with a variety of shifts in meaning and context.</Note_Text>
